cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of automatically classifying and searching memes in a large dataset, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), social media analysis (SI), and multimedia (MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IR, which covers research on search engines, information retrieval, and web search. The second likely category is cs.CL, which deals with research on computational linguistics, including text classification, sentiment analysis, and information extraction. The third likely category is cs.CV, which covers research on computer vision, including image classification, object recognition, and visual search. The fourth likely category is cs.SI, which covers research on social and information networks, including social media analysis, recommendation systems, and user behavior modeling. The fifth likely category is cs.MM, which covers research on multimedia, including image and video processing, multimedia retrieval, and multimedia analytics.
